iano plains (Italy) derived from the elevations of the Last Interglacial Highstand data (2003) J. Quat. Sci., 18, pp. 13-27; Giordano, G., The sedimentation along the Roman coast between middle and upper Pleistocene: The interplay of eustatism, tectonics and volcanism. New data and review (2003) Il Quat., 16, pp. 115-121; Dai Pra, G., Oscillazioni del livello marino, depositi e morfogenesi continentali nelle isole pontine (Italia Centrale) (1994) Geogr. Fis. Din. Quat., 17, pp. 139-153; Lambeck, K., Bard, E., Sea-level change along the French Mediterranean coast for the past 30 000 years (2000) Earth Planet. Sci. Lett., 175, pp. 203-222; Lambeck, K., Antonioli, F., Purcell, A., Silenzi, S., Sea level change along the Italian coast for the past 10,000 years (2004) Quat. Sci. Rev., 23, pp. 1567-1598; Lambeck, K., Sea-level change and shore-line evolution in Aegean Greece since Upper Palaeolithic time (1996) Antiquity, 70, pp. 588-611; Sivan, D., Lambeck, K., Galili, E., Raban, A., Holocene sea-level changes along the Mediterranean coast of Israel, based on archaeological observations and numerical model (2001) Palaeogeogr. Palaeoclimatol. Palaeoecol., 167, pp. 101-117; Mitrovica, J.X., Davis, J.L., Present-day post-glacial sea level change far from the Late Pleistocene ice sheets: Implications for recent analysis of tide gauge records (1995) Geophys. Res. Lett., 22, pp. 2529-2532; Lambeck, K., Purcell, A., Johnston, P., Nakada, M., Yokoyama, Y., Water-load definition in the glacio-hydro-isostatic sea-level equation (2003) Quat. Sci. Rev., 22, pp. 309-318; Nakada, M., Lambeck, K., The melting history of the late Pleistocene Antarctic ice sheet (1998) Nature, 333, pp. 36-40; Lambeck, K., Sea level change from mid-Holocene to recent time: An Australian example with global implications (2001) American Geophysical Union Geodynamics Series, 29, pp. 33-50; Stone, J.O., Holocene deglaciation of Marie Byrd Land, West Antarctica (2003) Science, 299, pp. 99-102; http://www.pol.a